Section 1:
1 L.D. 411
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 265, L.D. 411, “An Act to Amend the
10 Law Governing the Disposition of Forfeited Firearms”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Directing the Attorney General to Update Rules Relating to the Disposition
13 of Forfeited Firearms'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. Attorney General to update rules. Resolved: That the Attorney General
16 shall update the rules regarding the disposition of forfeited firearms to clarify that the
17 proceeds from the auctioning of forfeited firearms by the State must be placed in the Safe
18 Homes Program Fund pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 25, section 7001,
19 subsection 4, except that the Department of Administrative and Financial Services may
20 retain 12% of the proceeds and the Department of Public Safety, Maine State Police,
21 sherriff's departments and municipal police departments may retain the proceeds resulting
22 from the auction of firearms forfeited to their respective departments.'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment strikes the bill and replaces it with a resolve directing the Attorney
2277 General to update the rules relating to the disposition of forfeited firearms to clarify that all
2288 proceeds from the auction of forfeited firearms go to the Safe Homes Program except that
2299 the Department of Administrative and Financial Services may retain 12% of the total
3300 proceeds and the Department of Public Safety, Maine State Police, sherriff's departments
3311 and municipal police departments may retain the proceeds resulting from the auction of
3322 firearms forfeited to their respective departments.
3333 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3344 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR0868(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
